Payne","target":"Author/Matthew S. Payne","line":99},{"title":"Author/Matthew Payne","target":"Author/Matthew Payne","line":100},{"title":"Author/Paul Sheean","target":"Author/Paul Sheean","line":101},{"title":"Author/Paul Sheean","target":"Author/Paul Sheean","line":102},{"title":"Author/Pascal Vallotton","target":"Author/Pascal Vallotton","line":103},{"title":"Author/Pascal Vallotton","target":"Author/Pascal Vallotton","line":104},{"title":"Author/Dimitrios Zabaras","target":"Author/Dimitrios Zabaras","line":105},{"title":"Author/Dimitrios Zabaras","target":"Author/Dimitrios Zabaras","line":106},{"title":"Author/M. K. Bird","target":"Author/M. K. Bird","line":107},{"title":"Author/Michael Bird","target":"Author/Michael Bird","line":108},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/bennett_vitamin_2013/bennett_vitamin_2013.pdf","line":110}],"metadata":{"id":"bennett_vitamin_2013","type":"article-journal","title":"Vitamin D2-Enriched Button Mushroom (Agaricus bisporus) Improves Memory in Both Wild Type and APPswe/PS1dE9 Transgenic Mice","issued":{"date-parts":[[2013]]},"DOI":"10.1371/journal.pone.0076362","container-title":"PLOS ONE","abstract":"Vitamin D deficiency is widespread, affecting over 30% of adult Australians, and increasing up to 80% for at-risk groups including the elderly (age>65). The role for Vitamin D in development of the central nervous system is supported by the association between Vitamin D deficiency and incidence of neurological and psychiatric disorders including Alzheimer’s disease (AD). A reported positive relationship between Vitamin D status and cognitive performance suggests that restoring Vitamin D status might provide a cognitive benefit to those with Vitamin D deficiency. Mushrooms are a rich source of ergosterol, which can be converted to Vitamin D2 by treatment with UV light, presenting a new and convenient dietary source of Vitamin D2. We hypothesised that Vitamin D2-enriched mushrooms (VDM) could prevent the cognitive and pathological abnormalities associated with dementia. Two month old wild type (B6C3) and AD transgenic (APPSwe/PS1dE9) mice were fed a diet either deficient in Vitamin D2 or a diet which was supplemented with VDM, containing 1±0.2 µg/kg (∼54 IU/kg) vitamin D2, for 7 months. Effects of the dietary intervention on memory were assessed pre- and post-feeding. Brain sections were evaluated for amyloid β (Aβ) plaque loads and inflammation biomarkers using immuno-histochemical methods. Plasma vitamin D metabolites, Aβ40, Aβ42, calcium, protein and cholesterol were measured using biochemical assays. Compared with mice on the control diet, VDM-fed wild type and AD transgenic mice displayed improved learning and memory, had significantly reduced amyloid plaque load and glial fibrillary acidic protein, and elevated interleukin-10 in the brain. The results suggest that VDM might provide a dietary source of Vitamin D2 and other bioactives for preventing memory-impairment in dementia. This study supports the need for a randomised clinical trial to determine whether or not VDM consumption can benefit cognitive performance in the wider population.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Bennett","given":"Louise","literal":""},{"family":"Bennett","given":"Louise","literal":""},{"family":"Kersaitis","given":"Cindy","literal":""},{"family":"Kersaitis","given":"Cindy","literal":""},{"family":"Macaulay","given":"S. Lance","literal":""},{"family":"Macaulay","given":"S. L.","literal":""},{"family":"Münch","given":"Gerald","literal":""},{"family":"Münch","given":"Gerald","literal":""},{"family":"Niedermayer","given":"Garry","literal":""},{"family":"Niedermayer","given":"Garry","literal":""},{"family":"Nigro","given":"Julie","literal":""},{"family":"Nigro","given":"Julie","literal":""},{"family":"Payne","given":"Matthew S.","literal":""},{"family":"Payne","given":"Matthew","literal":""},{"family":"Sheean","given":"Paul","literal":""},{"family":"Sheean","given":"Paul","literal":""},{"family":"Vallotton","given":"Pascal","literal":""},{"family":"Vallotton","given":"Pascal","literal":""},{"family":"Zabaras","given":"Dimitrios","literal":""},{"family":"Zabaras","given":"Dimitrios","literal":""},{"family":"Bird","given":"M. K.","literal":""},{"family":"Bird","given":"Michael","literal":""}],"citation-key":"bennett_vitamin_2013","year":"2013","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Vitamin D2-Enriched Button Mushroom (Agaricus bisporus) Improves Memory in Both Wild Type and APPswe/PS1dE9 Transgenic Mice"],"author-links":["[[Author/Louise Bennett]]","[[Author/Louise Bennett]]","[[Author/Cindy Kersaitis]]","[[Author/Cindy Kersaitis]]","[[Author/S. Lance Macaulay]]","[[Author/S. L. Macaulay]]","[[Author/Gerald Münch]]","[[Author/Gerald Münch]]","[[Author/Garry Niedermayer]]","[[Author/Garry Niedermayer]]","[[Author/Julie Nigro]]","[[Author/Julie Nigro]]","[[Author/Matthew S. Payne]]","[[Author/Matthew Payne]]","[[Author/Paul Sheean]]","[[Author/Paul Sheean]]","[[Author/Pascal Vallotton]]","[[Author/Pascal Vallotton]]","[[Author/Dimitrios Zabaras]]","[[Author/Dimitrios Zabaras]]","[[Author/M. K. Bird]]","[[Author/Michael Bird]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/bennett_vitamin_2013/bennett_vitamin_2013.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"12ds6or","at":1774951890540}},"smart_blocks:Research/@bennett_vitamin_2013.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.00270933,-0.00476594,0.03217001,-0.04351477,-0.03836698,0.03113807,0.00483605,0.03509233,-0.07332829,-0.00144255,0.01354044,-0.07733109,0.08176863,0.02068193,0.05444385,0.0130904,0.01643604,0.00039687,-0.08804572,0.05143103,-0.02338248,-0.02792149,0.03203781,0.01889821,0.06012606,0.04366342,-0.0361633,-0.02625534,-0.04334842,-0.21792571,0.00273051,0.0028941,0.02218835,-0.08107626,-0.06691594,-0.03489391,0.04344724,0.00329692,-0.02228649,0.00177979,0.0992967,0.02466541,0.00870166,0.06537104,-0.06590731,-